{
  "texts": [
    "She struggled to even go for walks, even though she had many appointments at local hospitals and clinics.",
    "She became primarily housebound, with only short trips to the grocery store or to see a pet warden.",
    "She was reduced to having nearly 24hrs a day of assistance, administration of a nebulizer, and hospice nurses intervening if her symptoms increased.",
    "But the seasons turned, and so did Amelia's fate.",
    "One fateful autumn day, she received the news that would forever change her life: a diagnosis of a degenerative neurological condition."
  ]
}